580
00:38:51,519 --> 00:38:53,479
and then you can drop me off at the domestic one, okay?

581
00:38:53,480 --> 00:38:54,880
Are you even human?

582
00:38:56,199 --> 00:38:57,288
In one day,

583
00:38:57,289 --> 00:38:59,159
I have to send off two best friends.

584
00:38:59,599 --> 00:39:00,809
Who would be happy about that?

585
00:39:06,519 --> 00:39:07,840
Don't laugh. Hold it in.

586
00:39:07,960 --> 00:39:09,960
I know you yearn for the outside world.

587
00:39:10,329 --> 00:39:11,809
But I can't bear to leave you either.

588
00:39:13,559 --> 00:39:15,440
Then why are you laughing?

589
00:39:18,440 --> 00:39:19,718
Because I've been brooding.

590
00:39:19,719 --> 00:39:21,239
I realized I really couldn't cry.

591
00:39:22,880 --> 00:39:24,039
Remember to bring me a gift.

592
00:39:28,880 --> 00:39:29,920
Are they college students?

593
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:31,159
They are so young.

594
00:39:52,329 --> 00:39:53,400
They are really young.

595
00:39:54,440 --> 00:39:55,678
I'm so envious.

596
00:39:55,679 --> 00:39:57,289
Every time I think about being 26,

597
00:39:57,599 --> 00:39:58,639
I get a little scared.

598
00:39:59,079 --> 00:40:00,399
There's nothing to be envious of.

599
00:40:00,480 --> 00:40:04,360
Besides, we haven't wasted a single second of our prime time.

600
00:40:04,440 --> 00:40:05,559
That's right.

601
00:40:06,329 --> 00:40:08,329
Aren't we just halfway there?

602
00:40:08,400 --> 00:40:09,840
Not you. You're already there.

603
00:40:13,519 --> 00:40:14,768
- Let's go. - Let's go.

604
00:40:14,769 --> 00:40:15,840
Why are you so happy?

605
00:40:16,809 --> 00:40:17,960
What else can I do?

606
00:40:18,599 --> 00:40:20,519
Why do you still look sad?

607
00:40:21,000 --> 00:40:22,198
I'm not going then. I won't see you off.

608
00:40:22,199 --> 00:40:23,199
You should go.

609
00:40:23,200 --> 00:40:24,559
- No. - No.

610
00:40:25,559 --> 00:40:26,960
- Let's go. - I'm not going.

611
00:40:27,199 --> 00:40:28,289
I'm not going.

612
